COMMITTEE REPORT
Mr. Speaker: Your Committee on Judiciary, to which was referred
House Bill 1344, has had the same under consideration and begs leave
to report the same back to the House with the recommendation that said
bill be amended as follows:
Page 10, line 17, delete "forty" and insert "ten".
Page 10, line 18, delete "($40)." and insert "($10).".
Page 10, line 21, after "fee;" insert "or".
Page 10, line 22, delete "found to have committed an infraction; or"
and insert "required to pay a deferral fee;".
Page 10, delete line 23.
Page 10, line 24, after "of" insert "fifty dollars ($50).".
Page 10, delete line 25.
and when so amended that said bill do pass.
(Reference is to HB 1344 as introduced.)
JETER
Committee Vote: yeas 11, nays 0.
